        "subject": "LU-9066 ldlm: NOT evict client when target stopping",
        "message": "LU-9066 ldlm: NOT evict client when target stopping\n\nThe inflight LDLM AST RPC will get failure when the current target\nis stopping for failover or pure umount. Originally, the AST error\nhandler will call ldlm_failed_ast() to evict related lock holder.\nSuch process is improper under the race case, it will cause client\nerror after the service re-mounted.\n\nThis patch checks the obd device status, if it is in stopping, then\nNOT evict the client for the LDLM AST RPC error.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I12247b21314c46caabde86063eb66f8bc6dd2675\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
